    <h1 id="bookh1">Prenatal Care - 6th Month</h1>
    

    <h3>Nutrition</h3>
    <p>
        In the 6th month of pregnancy, your baby's growth is accelerating, and so is their nutritional needs. Here are some dietary recommendations:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Continue consuming a well-balanced diet with a variety of fruits, vegetables, and whole grains.</li>
        <li>Ensure you get enough iron and calcium for the baby's bone development and blood production.</li>
        <li>Consume foods rich in folic acid and fiber to support the baby's neural tube development and digestion.</li>
        <li>Stay hydrated by drinking plenty of water, especially as your blood volume increases.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Exercises</h3>
    <p>
        Staying active in the 6th month is essential for maintaining your well-being. Here are some safe exercises for pregnant women:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Low-impact aerobic exercises like brisk walking or swimming are still excellent choices.</li>
        <li>Prenatal yoga can help with relaxation, flexibility, and managing stress.</li>
        <li>Consider exercises that strengthen your pelvic floor muscles to prepare for labor and delivery.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        Always consult with your healthcare provider before starting any new exercise routine or making significant dietary changes.
    </p>

